#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_visualshadernodecustom.rst:82
msgid ""
"Override this method to define the actual shader code of the associated "
"custom node. The shader code should be returned as a string, which can "
"have multiple lines (the ``\"\"\"`` multiline string construct can be "
"used for convenience)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_visualshadernodecustom.rst:84
msgid ""
"The ``input_vars`` and ``output_vars`` arrays contain the string names of"
" the various input and output variables, as defined by ``_get_input_*`` "
"and ``_get_output_*`` virtual methods in this class."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_visualshadernodecustom.rst:86
msgid ""
"The output ports can be assigned values in the shader code. For example, "
"``return output_vars[0] + \" = \" + input_vars[0] + \";\"``."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_visualshadernodecustom.rst:88
msgid ""
